Berry Gratin with Lemon Sabayon
  --America's Test Kitchen

Sabayon:
1/4 c water
1/2 tsp grated lemon zest + 3 tbsp lemon juice (1 large lemon)
pinch table salt
3 large egg yolks
1/3 c sugar (2 1/3 oz)

Adjust oven rack to upper middle position and heat o 400F. Combine water, lemon zest, lemon juice, and salt in a small bowl and set aside. Whisk the egg yolks and sugar in a medium bowl until frothy, about 1 min. Set the bowl over a pan of simmering water. Continue whisking until the mixture begins to thicken, ~1 min. Gradually whisk in the lemon mixture and continue cooking, whisking constantly, until the mixture is thick, light yellow, and tripled in volume, 5-7 min. Remove the bowl from the saucepan, whisk constantly, ~30 s to cool, then set aside while preparing the berries. occasionally whisking the mixture.

Berries:
1 c fresh raspberries
1 c fresh blackberries
1 c fresh blueberries
3 tbsp sugar 

Combine the berries in a wide, shallow 2 quart broiler safe gratin dish or divide among 6 ramekins or individual gratin dishes set on a rimmed baking sheet. Bake the berries nutil the fruit is warm and just beginning to release its juices, ~8 min. Remove the berries from the oven. Spoon the lemon sabayon over the berries and sprinkle with the sugar. Ignite a kitchen torch and caramelize the sugar. Serve immediately.

Notes: can use any combination of berries, or single berry, just keep quantity the same.
